Viva / Interview Answer

The Face Mask Detection project uses images stored in the dataset folder to train a deep learning model through train_mask_detector.py. The trained model is saved as mask_detector.model. The files detect_mask_image.py and detect_mask_video.py use this model to detect whether a person is wearing a mask from images or real-time video. The remaining files provide documentation, dependencies, training graphs, and project guidelines.

